      • setLocation

        public boolean setLocation​(SimpleStoryLocation location,
                           StoryAction onSuccess,
                           StoryAction onError)
        Sets character location
        Be careful! If character current location is null then sets location regardless of entry condition
        Changes StateManager state to LOCATION_MOVE_START(current location) and then if current location is not null and has been successfully changed will change state to LOCATION_MOVE_COMPLETE(new location)
        Specified by:
        setLocation in interface AllSystemsCharacter<Long,​SimpleStoryCharacter,​SimpleStoryInventory,​SimpleStoryLocation,​SimpleStoryItem,​SimpleStoryQuest,​String>
        Parameters:
        location - new character location
        onSuccess - called if location successfully changes
        onError - called if location not changed
        Returns:
        true if location has been changed
